results.label: Sculpteo
results.description: Sculpteo is a French company specialized in 3D printing in the cloud. Sculpteo offers an online 3D printing service, using rapid prototyping and a manufacturing process involving laser sintering or stereo lithography. The company was founded in June 2009 by Eric Carreel co-founder of Inventel, acquired by Technicolor in 2005 and Withings, Clement Moreau and Jacques Lewiner.
